Doesn't work for Windows 7 Ultimate x64 bit.  Tried many, many times, and it keeps telling me to close the application when nothing is running except the Keygen.  It seems to be fucking with the registry in a way that prevents it from doing anything.  Lame.

I retract my previous comment.  Apparently you can't install Protected Folder along with it.  Otherwise it will not work.  After cleaning the registry with CCleaner and uninstalling PF it worked.  Very strange, but at least it worked.  Thanks Anacondaz.

The problem with Windows 7 64bit is as follows:

System retains serial as long as the program is not shut down, or the system is abruptly turned off (like when you lose power briefly). When this happens, the program reverts back to the "free" version when it is restarted.
